1	Product 0	\N	published	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "youtube", "format": "", "version": 1, "videoID": "CZ7a-dx3Glw"}, {"tag": "h1", "type": "heading", "format": "start", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "What is Payload?", "type": "text", "style": "background-color: #ffffff;color: #4a90e2;", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Payload is a headless CMS and application framework. It's meant to provide a massive boost to your development process, but importantly, stay out of your way as your apps get more complex.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Payload 2.0 has been released!", "type": "text", "style": "background-color: #d0021b;color: #ffffff;", "detail": 0, "format": 1, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Includes Postgres support, Live Preview, Lexical Editor, and more.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}, {"type": "link", "fields": {"doc": null, "url": "https://payloadcms.com/blog/payload-2-0", "newTab": false, "linkType": "custom"}, "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 2, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Read the announcement", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"mode": "normal", "text": ".", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Out of the box, Payload gives you a lot of the things that you often need when developing a new website, web app, or native app:", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"tag": "ul", "type": "list", "start": 1, "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "listitem", "value": 1, "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "A database to store your data (Postgres and MongoDB supported)", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "listitem", "value": 2, "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "A way to store, retrieve, and manipulate data of any shape via full REST and GraphQL APIs", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "listitem", "value": 3, "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Authenticationcomplete with commonly required functionality like registration, email verification, login, & password reset", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "listitem", "value": 4, "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Deep access control to your data, based on document or field-level functions", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "listitem", "value": 5, "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "File storage and access control", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "listitem", "value": 6, "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "A beautiful admin UI that's generated specifically to suit your data", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}], "listType": "bullet", "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "link", "fields": {"doc": null, "url": "https://payloadcms.com/docs/getting-started/what-is-payload#what-does-headless-mean", "newTab": false, "linkType": "custom"}, "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 2, "children": [{"tag": "h2", "type": "heading", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "What does \\"headless\\" mean?", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}], "direction": "ltr"}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "A headless CMS is a system that sticks to what it's good atmanaging content. It concentrates solely on granting administrators an effective way to author and maintain content, but doesn't control how and where that content is used.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "In this way, the CMS can ensure that its content editing experience is highly polished and effective while avoiding placing creative constraints on designers or restricting development teams. In contrast, traditional content management systems bind the presentation of your content to the storage of your content and severely limit the creativity, development and usability of the content that they manage.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "At this point this concept is", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}, {"type": "link", "fields": {"doc": null, "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Headless_content_management_system", "newTab": false, "linkType": "custom"